One in three women around the world will experience some form of violence during their lifetime.Less than 40 per cent of women who experience violence seek help. Violence against women remains the least discussed act of human rights violation. One in three women around the world will experience some form of violence during their lifetime regardless of cultural or geographical boundaries.
It is deep-rooted in the gender inequality and stereotypes that women have been subjected to for ages.



