In agreement with the UN women’s report, this year has been like no other. Even before Covid-19 hit, violence against women and girls had reached pandemic proportions with 243 million women and girls having been abused globally by an intimate partner in the past year.
Less than 40 per cent of women who experience violence seek help. The World Health Organization has also reported a high prevalence of GBV during the pandemic. Indeed, GBV has been deprioritised, leaving vulnerable groups at higher risk.



