Victims experience blame, shame and stigma in most cases causing long-term negative effects on their physical and mental health. It becomes a barrier to social, political and economic development.
These experiences cause an increased likelihood of poor mental health manifested by anxiety, depression, suicide, homicide, psychoactive substance abuse and further violence to mention but a few.
We need to cultivate a culture of mutual respect and gender equality. Taking pro-active steps in addressing GBV will safeguard the physical and mental health of women and girls. 
